      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The short narrative is condensed, animated, graphic,[58] not subjected to elaboration, against which view the mention of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Andrew",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", whom Matthew and Luke omit as a secondary person, cannot well be urged. Comp. Weiss, p. 654.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "[58] In this point of view the sickness is denoted by the words ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "κατέκειτο πυρέσσ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". as severe enough not to allow the event to be treated as a simple soothing of the over-excited nervous system (Schenkel). Mere psychological soothings of this kind would simply stand in utter disproportion to the sensation produced by Jesus as a worker of miracles.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      },
